Description: 2012 Fender Kurt Cobain Signature Jaguar Here is a very cool Kurt Cobain Jaguar! Only a small number of these got the factory relic treatment like this one. Every nick and scratch matches up with the ones left by Kurt on his original! The serial number starts with "MX12" which dates it to 2012. It features an Alder body with gloss urethane 3-color sunburst finish. The neck is maple with a bound rosewood fretboard and it has the Modern C profile with a 9.5" radius. The pickups are DiMarzio PAF DP-103 36th Anniversary Humbuckers. Actual weight is 8 lbs 11 oz.The body is in very good condition overall with no additional dings or scratches other than the ones put on by in the factory. No cracks, modifications or structural issues. The neck is straight and the frets show only a touch of wear. It's in excellent playing condition with no dead frets or other major issues. The fretboard, back of the neck and headstock have no additional dings or scratches other than the ones put on it by the factory. No cracks, repairs or modifications.The hardware and electronics are original and in excellent working condition. It comes with the original G&G case which has some minor wear on the outside. All of the latches, hinges and handle are in excellent working order and the interior has no bad odors. The original book and case accessories are included. This guitar is listed on Reverb also.
